article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — CJ Huntley had 22 points in Appalachian State's 93-81 victory against Queens on Wednesday night. Huntley had eight rebounds for the Mountaineers (8-2). Donovan Gregory added 22 points while finishing 9 of 10 from the floor, and he also had five assists and three steals. Tre'Von Spillers had 16 points and shot 8 of 10 from the field. The Mountaineers picked up their seventh straight victory. The Royals (6-6) were led in scoring by Deyton Albury, who finished with 25 points and four assists. Queens also got 19 points and two steals from AJ McKee. In addition, BJ McLaurin had 18 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
